overview: "The user initiated a review of a sleep questionnaire application,
  providing a detailed specification. The agent systematically analyzed the
  existing codebase against the requirements and generated a plan to address
  identified gaps. The initial phase of implementation focused on critical
  features: adding a 1-10 severity scale for tiredness with associated safety
  warnings, implementing detection logic for COMISA (Comorbid Insomnia and Sleep
  Apnea) and Insufficient Sleep Syndrome, and integrating a comprehensive set of
  placeholder outbound links to relevant sleep and mental health resources
  within both the interactive and PDF reports. The agent updated the types,
  validation schemas, UI components, and report generation logic to incorporate
  these new features, ensuring the application aligns more closely with the
  user's detailed requirements."
